manifest_analysis.title:
Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.
manifest_analysis.name: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App [android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]

Permission: android.permission.INSTALL_PACKAGES
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. playstore_details.title: Browser Popup Detector - Block Ads In Browser
playstore_details.description:
Browser opened automatically but you don't know who did it?

Here comes Browser Popup Detector: 
It is a browser hijack detection app helps you catch the culprit of randomly browser ad pop-ups. 
It is also an adblock browser blocks banner and video ads.

Prerequisite:
Uninstall other third-party browsers and disable all system browsers. Only keep 'Browser Popup Detector' as the only one browser on your phone. (This step cannot skip,  because malicious apps can specify whatever browser they want to launch, Browser Popup Detector cannot catch the URL if it opens in other browsers.)

How it works:
1. Indicate the browser is opened by which app by displaying its name and icon so you can easily identify.
2. Click the app info will directly jump to the app details page.
3. Uninstall the app to terminate the browser ad pop-ups!

If you have any question or suggestion, feel free to contact me at ttdesignfeedback@gmail.com. I'll reply to you asap.
